Let $C$ be the Fermat curve of degree $d \geq 3$ in the projective plane $\mathbb{P}^2$ over $\mathbb{C}$, defined by the homogeneous polynomial $F_d = x^d + y^d + z^d$. The 2-Hessian of $C$ has a "core" given by the arrangement of lines $\mathcal{B}: (x^d - y^d)(y^d - z^d)(z^d - x^d) = 0$. The sextactic points of $C$ are points where there exists a hyperosculating conic. There are $3d^2$ sextactic points on $C$, clustered into three groups. One cluster of $d^2$ sextactic points has coordinates $s_{j,k} = (\zeta^j u^k : u^k : 2^{1/d})$ for $j \in \{0, \ldots, d-1\}$ and $k$ odd with $0 < k < 2d$, where $\zeta$ is a primitive $d$-th root of unity and $u$ is a $2d$-th root of unity satisfying $u^d = -1$. These $d^2$ sextactic points are distributed with $d$ points on each of the $d$ lines in $\mathcal{B}_z = V(x^d - y^d)$. For any line in $\mathcal{B}_z$, say $V(x - \zeta^j y)$ for a fixed $j$, there are exactly $d$ sextactic points on it, corresponding to the $d$ odd values of $k$. At each sextactic point $s_{j,k}$, the hyperosculating conic $O_{j,k}$ is given by the polynomial
\begin{align*}
O_{j,k} = &d(d+1)\zeta^{-2j}x^2 + d(d+1)y^2 - 4(d+1)(2d-3)u^{2k}2^{-2/d}z^2 \\
&- 2(d-2)(5d-3)\zeta^{-j}xy + 8d(d-2)\zeta^{-j}u^{k}2^{-1/d}xz + 8d(d-2)u^{k}2^{-1/d}yz.
\end{align*}
Consider the $d$ hyperosculating conics at the $d$ sextactic points that are co-linear on a fixed line in the core 2-Hessian lines $\mathcal{B}$. What is the number of common intersection points of these $d$ conics when $d > 3$, and what is the number when $d = 3$?

Consider the Diophantine equation
\begin{equation}
\tag{eq:bennetAB}
ax^p + by^p = z^2,
\end{equation}
where $p \geq 11$ is a prime, and $a$ and $b$ are coprime integers with $p \nmid ab$. Let $\alpha, \beta, \gamma \in \mathbb{Z}_{\geq 0}$ with $\alpha \geq 6$, and suppose that
$$ab = 2^{\alpha} s^{\beta} t^{\gamma},$$
where $(s,t)$ is one of the pairs $(3,31)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(5,11)$ (with $\alpha \geq 7$), $(5,19)$, $(5,23)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(7,19)$ (with $\gamma \geq 1$), $(11,13)$, $(11,23)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(11,29)$, $(11,31)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(13,31)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(19,23)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$), $(19,29)$, or $(29,31)$ (with $\beta \geq 1$). In addition, assume that the values of $ab$, $p$, and $\alpha$ are not those given in Table \ref{tb:ABvalseven}. 

Under these assumptions, what is the number of solutions in nonzero pairwise coprime integers $(x, y, z)$ to equation (eq:bennetAB)?

